ssfe on their syscons terminal (mnbsd is dropping pcvt, and the 386BSD-
derived family stays with SCO syscons instead of using NetBSD® wscons; the
native NT console used by Interix has similar issues, but luckily, Interix
already comes with an X11R5 xterm capable enough – if you have an X server,
that is)
